    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{6}{x^{2}-x-30}-\frac{x}{x^{2}-x-30}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{1}{x+5}, x\ne 6</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{6}{x^{2}-x-30}-\frac{x}{x^{2}-x-30}} 
      \amp = \frac{{6-x}}{{x^{2}-x-30}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{6-x}}{{\left(x-6\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-x+6}}{{\left(x-6\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-\left(x-6\right)}}{{\left(x-6\right)\mathopen{}\left(x+5\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{1}{x+5}, x\ne 6}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>x-6</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne {6}</m>.</p>
</solution>
